{
  "name": "Google Maps → verified emails → Google Sheets (Crawlora)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Google Maps → verified emails → Google Sheets\n\nPulls local businesses from Crawlora's Google Maps dataset (only the ones that have a website), finds each site's public business emails with the Contact API, and appends outreach-ready rows to your sheet. Crawlora handles the anti-bot scraping, so this does not break like DIY HTML-parsing flows.\n\n### Setup (3 steps)\n1. Add an **HTTP Header Auth** credential named `Crawlora API (x-api-key)` — Header **Name** `x-api-key`, **Value** = your key from https://crawlora.net (free: 2,000 credits/mo, no card).\n2. Edit the search in **Crawlora: Google Maps dataset search** (q / city / state / category / filters).\n3. Pick your spreadsheet in **Append lead to Google Sheet**.\n\nEach business with a website costs one Contact API call — you are charged on success.",
        "height": 430,
        "width": 470,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "11111111-1111-4111-8111-0000000000a1",
      "name": "Setup",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -360,
        120
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Why a dataset + Contact API, not raw scraping\n\nGoogle Maps listings have a name, phone, and website — but **no email**. This flow filters to businesses that have a website (`has_website=true`), then enriches each site for public emails, phones, and socials, each with a verification status. No proxies, no brittle selectors to maintain.",
        "height": 220,
        "width": 470,
        "color": 7
      },
      "id": "11111111-1111-4111-8111-0000000000a2",
      "name": "Why this is reliable",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -360,
        580
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "id": "11111111-1111-4111-8111-000000000001",
      "name": "When clicking 'Execute workflow'",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.manualTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        240,
        360
      ]
    },
